The paper deals with the problem of testing small set expansion in general graphs, which is a fundamental problem in computer science and has connections to various fields such as graph theory, coding theory, and complexity theory. The paper presents testers with two-sided error and one-sided error in the adjacency list model, which are important tools in the study of property testing. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.CC (Computational Complexity), and cs.CG (Computational Geometry). Additionally, the paper also has connections to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.LG (Machine Learning), as small set expansion has applications in these fields.
